	Procmail. And in case of newsgroup everything still comes to your
server anyway. Moreover, *any* USENET group quickly attracts a f*cking
slew of cluebies. Just look at c.o.l.misc, for example. And one more thing
- you can't crosspost to the maillist (well, no *easy* crossposting using
Joe Average Luserware) so we are mostly spared from alt.destroy.microsoft
crew here.
> Mailing lists should be converted to newsgroups as soon as they have gotten
